description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cardiovascular theme within the Biomedical Research unit/Clinical Trials and Evaluation Unit is responsible for the support and set-up of clinical trials, working at the interface between the University of Bristol and UHBristol. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Clinical Research Administrator to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will undertake as necessary a wide range of administrative, organisational, data entry tasks as well as sample handling and collection duties to facilitate the smooth day to day running of a number of clinical trials. You should possess good communication skills, have very good IT skills and an interest in research. A methodical/organised approach to work, the ability to deal with work of a highly confidential nature, the ability to work to deadlines and very good attention to detail are essential pre-requisites for being successful in the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Emma Hopkins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Research Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address emma.hopkins@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0117 3421144&lt;/p&gt;
